Dear Onalaska ISD Community,

School will resume tomorrow, August 28, 2020, for on-campus and remote/at-home instruction.
text:
Dear Onalaska ISD Community,

School will resume tomorrow, August 28, 2020, for on-campus and remote/at-home instruction.

post_text:
Dear Onalaska ISD Community,
In coordination with Polk County Office of Emergency Management, Onalaska ISD has been monitoring the potential for hazardous weather conditions created by Hurricane Laura. Out of an abundance of caution, Onalaska ISD campuses will be closed for instruction and extra-curricular activities on Wednesday, August 26th, and Thursday, August 27th. On-campus and remote instruction will be suspended on both days. It is our plan to return to school on Friday, August 28th. In the event that conditions do not allow for return, additional information will be provided through our call-out system, Facebook, our District Website, and local news media.

Due to the mandatory evacuations of counties to our South along the Gulf Coast, traffic in our community will greatly increase. This traffic may create delays for our buses this afternoon. Please stay safe and stay tuned for more information.

post_text: Wishing a Happy 4th of July to the staff, students, families, and members of our resilient and caring community!
shared_text:
Sam Houston Electric Cooperative
July 4 at 1:44 PM ·

Returning to the Onalaska area recently hit by the tornado, Sam Houston EC Line Technician Yancy Williams found an American flag flying atop a Co-op pole that is no longer in service. Yancy, a military veteran, saluted the flag and then proceeded to take down the service wire. The pole, however, remains in place and the flag still flies. Well done, Yancy Williams. Well done. All of us at Sam Houston Electric Cooperative wish you a safe and happy Fourth of July. #PowerOn

shared_text:
Onalaska Wildcat Athletics
June 29 at 4:49 PM ·

Onalaska athletes and families:

Our number one goal above everything else is always the safety of our kids. Our Administrative team has been constantly monitoring the COVID-19 situation across the state as well as the county and locally. As of today with all the information we have received of area districts having confirmed cases and the recommendations from the Governor, it is in the best interest of our athletes, school, and community to suspend summer workouts from June 29th through July 12th. We will continue to monitor the situation to hopefully open back up on July 13th. This is a precaution measure as we have not had any cases at our workouts. We appreciate all the positive attitudes and the great work our students have put in so far but we feel this is what is best.

Athletes be sure to continue to work on your own so we don’t lose the work you have been doing! Stay safe while we all get through this.

We look forward to seeing you all again in 2 weeks!

Thank you,

Nicholas Tyerman

post_text:
Pandemic Electronic Benefit Transfer (P-EBT) is a one-time food benefit for families who lost access to free or reduced-price meals due to school closures. Eligible P-EBT families will receive application instructions from schools in late May. The P-EBT application will open the first week of June.

P-EBT food benefits are for children who received SNAP food benefits for March 2020 AND children who are certified for free or reduced-price school meals during the 2019-20 Texas school year. For more information, visit: hhs.texas.gov/PEBT or visit our school website!

OISD Instructional
At-Home Learning

At this time, please disregard any at home learning online notifications that your child is receiving.

OISD has put on hold all at home instructional learning. All campuses are in the process of suspending all online Google Classroom lessons/activities from being assigned. Currently, students and parents do not need to worry about the completion of paper learning packets or Google Classroom/online learning assignments. Please take this time to take care of your families.

Additional information regarding instruction will be released at a later date.

post_text:
Update for meals beginning Monday:
Changes by the Texas Department of Agriculture will now allow Onalaska ISD to provide breakfast and lunch during the same delivery. No longer will you have to make two separate trips to pick up a breakfast and lunch! With that convenience now allowed, the curbside pickup and drop-off locations and times have been adjusted.

Breakfast/Lunch may be picked up at Onalaska Elementary from 8:30 - 10:00 a.m. The pickup location has been moved to the afternoon car rider location. The meals will be brought to you and you will not need to get out of your vehicle. Student(s) must be present to receive a meal.

Breakfast/Lunch may also be picked up at our drop-off locations. Student(s) must be present to receive a meal. Once again, we greatly appreciate the generosity and support of various local POA's, organizations, and businesses in allowing us to use their lots to facilitate some of these drop-off sites.

To view drop-off sites please click on the link below:

post_text: Onalaska ISD will remain closed through April 3rd as ordered by the Governor of Texas. Under the guidelines of the Texas Education Agency (TEA), we will continue to provide instructional supports to our students while at home as it is important for them to continue learning so they do not face the regression of academic skills. Information will be sent out this afternoon to explain procedures for picking up instructional support materials (technology/paper packets). Onalaska ISD appreciates the community's overwhelming support as we continue to focus on the safety and education of our students during these unprecedented times.

post_text:
This is National FFA week and we are celebrating the impact FFA has on members everyday!

Everyone can celebrate by taking part in the following dress up days:
Monday - Wear Blue and Gold
Tuesday - Hunter Safety Orange/Camo
Wednesday - Wear FFA apparel or a green shirt
Thursday - Dress as your future Ag Career
Friday - Flannel Friday

(hats and face paint are not allowed this week; all clothing should be in dress code)

OJSH will also be participating in community project by donating non-perishable food items such as canned goods, boxed foods, snacks, cereals and toiletries. The items can be donated in Mrs. Graham or Mrs. Robinson's classrooms. This project will begin on Tuesday.

Onalaska FFA
February 11 at 10:21 PM ·

While bringing the outdoors indoors due to the weather, Miss Richardson, our student teacher from SHSU, hit a home run today with her turf anatomy lesson in Turf Grass Management class. After drawing the structures of turf grass, students then individually rotated through stations to compare and contrast various types of turf brought in, as well as discussed their observations and findings in small and large groups. It was such a fun and interactive lesson that the students thoroughly enjoyed. Way to go Miss Richardson!!!

post_text:
Onalaska Robotics competed at Cinco Ranch High School in Katy today against 39 other 5A and 6A schools. This is the first year for OJSH to have a Robotics program and today was their first competition. They made it to the finals and finished 14th in the competition. We are so proud of the entire group and their teacher and coach, Ms. Wheeler. Thanks also to Ms. Kennedy for navigating the world of UIL Robotics. The team advances to the State competition in March.
Team members:
Robot driver - Ekzavier P.
Coach- Lane S.
Programmer - Hunter R. and Matthew F.
Engineering Notebook - Megan W. Alexis H. and Makenzie J.

Onalaska ISD offers a very special program for our community. The Kitty Club meets every Tuesday at 8:00 am at the Elementary Campus. This is a program for children ages 2-4 to prepare for school. There are wonderful activities they participate in each week. This week they celebrated "Donut Day". It was a great day of math learning with a sprinkle of fun. If you have a 2-4 year old child come join us next Tuesday. We would love to have you.

For more information about the program contact: Stephanie Schubert 936-646-1013

post_text:
Last week the OJSH teachers took part in the first annual Great Turkey Trot! Sunday night 6 turkeys lost all their feathers throughout the building. Teacher teams competed to find the feathers and write something they are thankful for before posting their feather on the turkey. The winning team earned lunch to be delivered after the Thanksgiving holiday. Congratulations to Team 3: Mrs. Graham, Mrs. Fletcher, Mr. Kelley, Mr. DeMars, Mrs. Robertson, Ms. Diefendorf, and Mrs. Newman.

This Thanksgiving we are thankful for our Wildcat students and parents. It is wonderful to work for an amazing district and community! Thank you Wildcats and Happy Thanksgiving!

post_text: Junior Senior High School Student Council cooked lunch for law enforcement officials on Thursday, October 10th, to show appreciation for the hard work and dedication these individuals show towards our community. Among those in attendance were Polk County Fire Marshall Jacob Chapman, OPD Sgt. Tammie Heeth, Polk County D.A. Investigator Tracy Galloway, 411th District County Bailiff Jessie Stanton, Polk County Deputy Terri Mayer, Polk County Detective Byron Dunaway, Polk County Corporal Liham White, Polk County Sheriff's Office Deputy Kayla Hemperly, Polk County Sheriff's Office Corporal Mark Dubose, and Polk County Sheriff's Office Deputy Bernita Langley. Not pictured were Onalaska Police Chief John Maddox, Onalaska Police Captain Lee Parrish, Onalaska Police Officer Brittany George, and Texas DPS Officer Chris Cain.

Onalaska Ag Department and FFA is proudly starting year #8 with assisting various entities in this service learning project program while fulfilling the #FFAmotto! 💙💛

post_text:
OJSH Pancake Dinner Fundraiser and Resource Night 5:30pm - 7:00pm

Come enjoy a Pancake Dinner for only $3 per person. Proceeds support student scholarships and incentives. While you are at the school, talk to teachers about resources available to help your student at home with Reading, Math, Science, and Social Studies. We will also be having our Annual Title 1 Parent Meeting.

You do not have to purchase a Pancake Dinner in order to participate in the Resource Night or Parent Meeting.

We look forward to everyone attending!

post_text: Onalaska ISD will be holding regularly scheduled classes tomorrow. The District is monitoring weather/transportation conditions and receiving updates from the Office of Emergency Management. In the event that conditions require a closure or delay, we will notify our community using the District web page, Facebook, and our parent notification system. Information will also be provided to our local radio station, 102.3 KETX and Houston TV Stations Channel 2 KPRC, Channel 11 KHOU, and Channel 13 KTRK.

post_text: The District makes the safety of our students and staff a priority in all decisions of school closure and weather-related matters. In the event of any closures or delays we will notify our community using the District web page, Facebook, and our parent notification system. Information will also be provided to our local radio station, 102.3 KETX and Houston TV Stations Channel 2 KPRC, Channel 11 KHOU, and Channel 13 KTRK. We are closely monitoring the current weather situation and receiving updates from the Office of Emergency Management. We will share any changes to our schedule as quickly as possible.

post_text: Onalaska Proud!
shared_text:
Onalaska JROTC LDC
September 11, 2019 at 10:25 AM ·

Hello Everyone,

I am happy to say that the Onalaska Wildcat JROTC-LDC program will be adopting a highway! We will be responsible for cleaning a 2 mile stretch on US 190 about a mile east of FM 3152.. We will be required to clean up the HWY at least 4 times per year and our name will placed on a 4 x 4 sign on each end of the adopted HWY..Our agreement with TxDOT is pending signatures and we will be on our way to "Make a Difference"..

1SG Garcia

post_text:
LIGHTS⭐️CAMERA📽ACTION🎬

🐾❗️Tomorrow's THE DAY and we are so EXCITED to have our Wildcats Back!❗️🐾

Below you will find a few key things to help you and your Wildcat with their First Day:

🔴Doors open at 7:15 and breakfast will be served!
◼️If you are dropping your Wildcat off, you will enter the circle lot on the backside of the school near the police station.
🔴If you plan to walk your Wildcat in, please park in a safe place on the Bonner Park side. Please do not block any roadways or parking spots and you must escort your little one in.
◼️If you plan to join us for lunch, you will need your picture ID to enter the building.
🔴Our day ends at 3:30. If you are picking your little one up in the car rider line, the line forms down 356, towards The First Baptist Church and will proceed to the front of the school near Bonner Park.

✏️📚We look forward to tomorrow and a great 2019-2020 School Year!

shared_text:
Onalaska FFA
July 18, 2019 at 9:12 PM ·

The Golden Horizon Chapter Recognition is a state award that recognizes well-rounded local FFA chapters that have an inclusive, progressive, aggressive program of activities that promotes maximum participation in order to deliver the leadership component of agricultural education. Chapters are recognized within Single Teacher and Multiple Teacher divisions. Chapters are placed into Gold, Silver and Bronze categories, with the top 25% of chapters in each teacher division receiving a Gold Ranking. If Onalaska FFA's Program of Activities or student AND advisor involvement is ever considered "average" please refer to their accomplishments throughout this past school year. It takes long hours and pure dedication to be honored as one of the top chapters in the state! Onalaska FFA received a GOLD rating and was recognized on stage this afternoon during the 6th general session of the 2019 Texas FFA Convention in Fort Worth. There were only 26 total FFA chapters throughout the state that were honored with this Gold-rated distinction. CONGRATULATIONS, ONALASKA FFA!!!
🎉🎉🎉

post_text: In memory of the tragic events of 9/11 the JSHS foyer has arranged several displays to remember the 2,996 lives lost, the over 6,000 injured and to cultivate a respect for the magnitude of the attack. For many in our student body this was not a moment that lives in their memories, but a historical event that predates them. It is as a collective nation that we must "Never Forget".

post_text: Thank you for an outstanding first day. The bells will ring in about 30 minutes to close out day one. 1115 students attended classes today. Several parents have contacted the district and additional students will be enrolling as the week moves forward. The staff at Onalaska Elementary School and Onalaska Jr/Sr High School as well as the entire district staff is honored to be serving you and your students. Our prayer for everyone is to have a rewarding year filled with academic achievement as well as social and emotional growth. Our purpose is to keep your children safe, educate them and to help them develop into outstanding young people who will be tomorrow's Onalaska leaders. If we can be of service to you please contact us.

shared_text:
Onalaska FFA
July 15, 2018 at 9:46 PM ·

The Golden Horizon Chapter Recognition is a state award that recognizes well-rounded local FFA chapters that have an inclusive, progressive, aggressive program of activities that promotes maximum participation in order to deliver the leadership component of agricultural education. Chapters are recognized within Single Teacher and Multiple Teacher divisions. Chapters are placed into Gold, Silver and Bronze categories, with the top 25% of chapters in each teacher division receiving a Gold Ranking. If Onalaska FFA's Program of Activities or student AND advisor involvement is ever considered "average" please refer to their accomplishments throughout this past school year. It takes long hours and pure dedication to be honored as one of the top chapters in the state! Onalaska FFA received a GOLD rating and was recognized on stage during the 6th general session of the 90th annual Texas FFA Convention. We are thrilled at this accomplishment and are beyond proud of our chapter members who made this recognition possible!
